Enforcement coordination between different regulatory levels varies significantly between markets. Some jurisdictions have cooperative agreements that share inspection information and coordinate enforcement actions. Others operate independently with little communication between regulatory agencies. Companies quickly learn which jurisdictions have active enforcement and which rely primarily on complaint-driven oversight.

