Medical certification requirements ensure drivers can safely operate commercial vehicles, but the examination standards and physician qualifications vary significantly. Some companies use occupational medicine specialists familiar with commercial driver requirements, while others accept examinations from any licensed physician. Medical certification quality affects passenger safety, but regulatory oversight of examining physicians is minimal.

