Commercial vehicle inspection requirements mandate periodic safety inspections by certified mechanics, but inspection quality and thoroughness vary significantly between inspection facilities and individual inspectors. Some inspections involve comprehensive mechanical examination with detailed testing of brake systems, steering components, and safety equipment. Others focus primarily on obvious defects and paperwork compliance.

Maintenance documentation requirements establish record-keeping standards for vehicle servicing, repairs, and safety inspections. Companies must maintain records showing compliance with manufacturer maintenance schedules and regulatory inspection requirements. However, documentation quality ranges from comprehensive maintenance tracking systems to minimal paperwork that meets technical requirements without reflecting actual maintenance practices.

