Appeal procedures allow companies to contest audit findings and penalty assessments, but appeal success rates vary significantly between violation types and regulatory agencies. Companies learn which violations are worth contesting and which penalties are better accepted. Appeal processes can delay corrective actions and extend periods where safety problems remain unaddressed.

